metadata.name: Take Aim #1
metadata.description:
In Take Aim, the basic concept is obfuscation of a familiar image with another. In this case we obfuscate shaped bands with a grid or partial grid. The bands resemble targets, with the grid conversely resembling those things in life which stop us from achieving our goals. Although initially it appears that not achieving oneâ€™s target should be seen as a negative, in many ways I see this as a positive piece. I have learned that events which get in the way of our goals are often the very things that make life so rewarding.
